Subject: Re: [T2] Stranded - Bad Starter? HELP!

On Thu, Dec 26, 2002 at 08:25:38AM -0700, Jason Z Upper wrote:
> Symptoms: Key in, turn to Start, no sound.  Voltage is at 12v, idiot lights 
> go on, but nothing - not even a click - from the starter.  I bridged across 
> the starter terminals, and the starter runs (whizzzz!), but it doesn't 
> engage the flywheel.  I heated the starter and solenoid with a torch to 
> un-freeze anything that might be frozen, but still had the same results - 
> no luck.

What is the condition of the battery? New one? Cold weather (or rather
all the extra stuff we run when cold) can help kill a marginal batter.
Do you have the same results with the battery hooked up with jumper
cables to a running vehicle? Give these a try first. The cold weather
may have just accented a bad battery for you.
 
> Questions: Is the solenoid bad?  Is the starter bad?  Is the wiring bad?  
> Should the starter engage and start the engine if I bridge across the 
> starter terminals?  Is there anybody in the greater Boston area that has a 
> good starter for cheap?  Can I replace the starter with the engine and 
> trans in the car?

Yes you can remove it with all that in the bus. 2 bolts & a few
electrical connections to remove, then replace.

